sql:
SELECT COUNT(*) AS total_cyclists_in_category
FROM cyclists
WHERE category = 'Cat 1';

SELECT category, COUNT(*) AS total_cyclists
FROM cyclists
GROUP BY category;

external_knowledge:
- 'First team' refers to the team with team_id = 1;
- 'Names' here refer to the combination of first name and last name;
- 'Younger members' implies the order is from the earliest to the latest date of birth.

sql:
SELECT first_name
FROM cyclists
ORDER BY date_of_birth ASC;

SELECT average_speed
FROM race_analytics
WHERE average_speed > 20;

SELECT COUNT(*) AS cyclist_count, 'Cat 1' AS category
FROM cyclists
WHERE category = 'Cat 1';

SELECT AVG(average_speed) AS typical_racing_speed
FROM race_analytics
WHERE average_speed > 20 AND elevation_gain > 500;
